    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.001 Selassie I/374: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Emperor of Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Haile Selassie I</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="32" xml:id="d129fn32">Copy sent to the Department by the President’s
                        personal secretary, Miss Grace Tully.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-28">July 28,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My Government and people are anxious to assume the obligations of the United
                    Nations pact.<note n="33" xml:id="d129fn33">Declaration by the United Nations,
                        January 1, 1942, <ref target="frus1942v01#pg_25">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >i</hi>, p. 25</ref>.</note> We the first nation to regain its
                    freedom and independence wish to place the military and economic resources of
                    our country at the disposal of those nations who gladly sacrifice all for
                    liberty and justice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Haile Selassie</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
